; Regression test for issue #1638: Selinger's multiple currency accounting
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/1638
;
; Tests that double-entry consistency holds across currency exchanges using
; the {= price} (fixated price) syntax with an Income:Currency account.

P 2011/01/03 USD 1.30 CAD
P 2011/01/08 USD 1.45 CAD

2011/01/01 Opening balance
    Assets:Canadian_Cash        200 CAD
    Equity:Initial_Capital

2011/01/02 Exchange
    Assets:Canadian_Cash       -120 CAD
    Assets:US_Cash              100 USD
    Income:Currency

2011/01/03 Buy food
    Assets:US_Cash              -40 USD
    Expenses:Food                40 USD {= 1.3 CAD}
    Income:Currency

2011/01/05 Exchange
    Assets:US_Cash              -60 USD
    Assets:Canadian_Cash         75 CAD
    Income:Currency

2011/01/07 Buy food
    Assets:Canadian_Cash        -20 CAD
    Expenses:Food

; bal should net to zero with fixated prices and Income:Currency
test bal
          135.00 CAD  Assets:Canadian_Cash
         -200.00 CAD  Equity:Initial_Capital
           20.00 CAD
              40 USD  Expenses:Food
           45.00 CAD
             -40 USD  Income:Currency
--------------------
                   0
end test

; --basis should also net to zero
test bal --basis
          135.00 CAD  Assets:Canadian_Cash
         -200.00 CAD  Equity:Initial_Capital
           72.00 CAD  Expenses:Food
           -7.00 CAD  Income:Currency
--------------------
                   0
end test

; -X CAD should also net to zero
test bal -X CAD
          135.00 CAD  Assets:Canadian_Cash
         -200.00 CAD  Equity:Initial_Capital
           72.00 CAD  Expenses:Food
           -7.00 CAD  Income:Currency
--------------------
                   0
end test
